{
  "texts": [
    "This is because SBFL considers test execution differences, which in this case revealed a few more methods in the codebase that are related to the issue.",
    "With these newly revealed hints, the agent decides to invoke APIs to search for the resolve_related_fields and _prepare_related_fields_for_save methods (the latter method is actually where the developer chose to fix this bug 6).",
    "Moreover, we observe that the agent does not solely rely on the SBFL results to make API invocations.",
    "Instead of searching for methods ranked as top-1 in the SBFL results, the agent searched for the 3rd and 5th ranked methods.",
    "These methods are more related to some other hints mentioned in the issue description (highlighted in yellow), and the LLM agent is able to exploit this correlation between the natural language descriptions and the SBFL analysis results."
  ]
}